==English==

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A mark left by something that has passed along; as, the track, or wake, of a ship; the track of a meteor; the track of a sled or a wheel.
# A mark or impression left by the foot, either of man or beast; trace; vestige; footprint.
# The entire lower surface of the foot; -- said of birds, etc.
# A road; a beaten path.
# Course; way; as, the track of a comet.
# A path or course laid out for a race, for exercise, etc.
# The permanent way; the rails.
# A tract or area, as of land.
# The distance between the centerlines of two tires, measured where the tires contact the surface of the road. Automotive terminology, also sometimes 'track width'.
# {{cricket}} The [[pitch]].
# Sound stored on a record (or the physical track on one).
# Circular (never-ending) data storage unit on a side of magnetic or optical disk, divided into [[sector|sectors]].

